g.text: You: "I cannot. I cannot live without this job... fuck you then! And fuck me! I'll go."
Jean Vicquemare: "You manipulative fuck... Fine. It's cold and we have vehicles in the square. And the perp needs to be taken into custody too -- let's get a move on."
Jean Vicquemare: "I don't *want* to. But you discovered a new species. And solved the murder..." He shrugs.
Jean Vicquemare: "No." There's a silence. "Sure, you got the case together -- you can *do* policework -- in bouts. That's not a surprise to me."
Esprit de Corps: And Station 41 and the glow of its desk lamps, the clicking of coffee mugs, clouds of cigarette smoke and the ringing telephone... your youth. There is still a way back.
Reaction Speed: The houses, the streets, the motorways singing. Hold on. This is a fight we can *win*.
Esprit de Corps: You haven't been drinking, she thinks. So maybe this time...
Trant Heidelstam: "Agreed. The public relations potential of this is too valuable to let go."
You: "No way. I was a natural philosopher."

Empathy: His smirk suggests barely contained laughter.
Jean Vicquemare: "Yeah... Or seven? You're not doing too good there. It's an old-man thing. Two *old-years* equals one normal year. That -- and Dora Ingerlund really tore you a new one. A big one."
Jean Vicquemare: "I think she taught in the Académie des Arts, east of the river. Way east. Hard to say which came first -- the middle class chick or the drink? Egg and the chicken kinda thing..."

Jean Vicquemare: "My point is, you need to see a *psychiatrist* about this shit. Not a psychologist -- several degrees harder. Is there's something harder than a psychiatrist?" He pauses to think. "A forensic psychiatrist. Go talk to that."
You: "An iconic duo I take it?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "Detective, we just stopped a small-scale war. Something is happening to Revachol." He takes a look around -- into the deepening shadows of the streets -- then pulls up his collar.

Kim Kitsuragi: "Detective, we just stopped a small-scale war. Something is happening to Revachol." He pulls up his collar and looks around, the cold spring light reflected in the lenses of his glasses.
Kim Kitsuragi: "No -- good luck with *your* report." The lieutenant smiles warmly.
Encyclopedia: She lives at 1113 Tabernacle Road, in Jamrock. Remember?
You: "Yeah... no. You're staying here, Cuno. You're too young."
Cuno: "THE FUCK?!" He spreads his arms. "Cuno's been *seen* with you, out in the open. He's free game right now. Singin' to the popophone. Fuckin' informant shit. Got pig all over me -- smoked pig."

Cuno: "I won't say it! I won't say it anymore."
Physical Instrument: How you're able to perform a 360-degree spin-kick despite your less than stellar workout routine.
You: "Are you *seriously* using this moment to assert male privilege!?!"
Inland Empire: Compared to the intersection, in front of Video Revachol 24 -- it's nothing. Compared to that, everything is possible.
Perception (Sight): Think! You can *detect*. In Jamrock. Boogie Street. Couron. Le Royaume, underground. Coal City. On the 8/81-- it will all be yours to sieve through when the last snow has melted.
Jean Vicquemare: "Well -- obviously you're not a gym teacher anymore, but..."
Jean Vicquemare: "Well -- now you're a cop," he pauses, "or... not anymore, so I guess you're a gym teacher again."
Judit Minot: "Before you were a cop, you were a gym teacher in Couron." She looks around. "It's getting really cold outside. Should we maybe..."
You: "The collection of FALN sportswear I've amassed..."
Cuno: "Your lame taste in music. Like from -- the Forties. Even the way you *stand* and stretch and shit... Cuno's seen this shit before. In *gym* class."
"How you spin-kicked the kipt out, gymnast style... Cuno's seen this shit before. In *gym* class."
"How you jumped that shit, climbed to the roof... Cuno's seen this shit before. In *gym* class."
You: "Was she called Dora Du Bois?"
Jean Vicquemare: "Du Bois?" He shakes his head. "It was... Dora Ingerlund, I think. You've said her name. But you weren't married. You were engaged."
You: "No? Because a suspect seemed to think..."
Jean Vicquemare: "You're too unstable to work for a mob boss. You're suicidal, Harry. No mob boss would take you."
Judit Minot: "He's telling the truth. You were a gym teacher in Couron." She looks around. "It's getting really cold outside. Should we maybe..."
Conceptualization: They *are* damn iconic though -- Torson and McLaine!
Jean Vicquemare: "Yeah -- not like *us*. Two clinically depressed old men. Where's the contrast here? We're garbage."
Judit Minot: "Jamrock is the largest ghetto in Revachol. Faubourg, technically... but it's divided into *eleven* districts. Jamrock only has us."
Cuno: "Cuno's likin' this shit. Jamrock is the real shit -- Martinaise is fucking white as balls. Sea-shit. This ain't a real ghetto."
Jean Vicquemare: "Thank you, Cuno. You bring light to my day."
Esprit de Corps: They speak of change. The city. The tension on the streets. They speak of the events of April and the blood on the streets in May.
Perception (Sight): It says: "Tensions rise in Terminal YC In light of the Débardeurs' strike in Terminal B, among representatives of heavy industry in Coal City..." you read.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Talk to Captain Pryce? I'd rather not ruffle the feathers of *two* captains with my doom-mongering."
You: "No, I meant *investigate*. Come work in Precinct 41."
Esprit de Corps: Would fit in? Am crazy enough? Can take the stress? He doesn't know how to finish the sentence.
Rhetoric: This truly came as a surprise to him. Not a bad one. But he's at a loss.
Cuno: "You gonna *lie* after what we just been through? Let Cuno refresh you: Cuno said he'd take your crippled ass to the island, if you take Cuno to Jamrock. Boatman Cuno."

Trant Heidelstam: "It's tough. One of the toughest addictions to overcome. Comparable *only* to heavy synthetic opiates. Even morphine is easier to kick than alcohol -- statistically. The odds are against him. Especially at his age."
Jean Vicquemare: He nods. "He's too old. He's been like this for too long. I've seen him try many times. It's a farce by now."
You: "My life is forfeit. All I'm good for is this work. I *will* quit."
Esprit de Corps: No one knows what to say. But they agree. Keeping you on the force endangers civilians.
You: "Okay then. Fuck it. I have a shack here. I don't need you all."
Jean Vicquemare: "Don't pity yourself. You've managed not to die thus far. You'll manage now."
Jean Vicquemare: "No," he remarks dryly, "a regular one."
Jean Vicquemare: "You've been on about Mike again?" The detective shakes his head. "I hate that guy."

Jean Vicquemare: "God, I don't know..." He thinks. "Six years ago? She was way before my time."
Jean Vicquemare: "I've only seen a picture -- but it's obvious you formed a real spiritual connection with how *pretty* she was. One you never recuperated from."
Encyclopedia: Vaasa is where beautiful and impossibly blonde people come from.
Suggestion: He's anything but a loser. Although he would like to be seen as one. It's cooler that way.

Esprit de Corps: A lowset house, windswept -- and without you. Traffic whooshes by...
You: "What happened? Why did we need to go there?"

Perception (Hearing): Your clearance will not go up while you're within earshot of the Union headquarters.
You: (Lower your voice.) "Jean, he has nothing."
You: "I'm sorry. We just can't. It's not possible."
You: "Jean. I want Cuno at our station, solving this shit."
You: "His dad's in a coma and his only friend is gone."
You: "He was good. On the island. He can do this."
Jean Vicquemare: "You have to be *fifteen* for the junior officer program -- you're not even that."
Cuno: "Hey, f****t! You don't get it. Cuno's got pig all over him -- Cuno smells of bacon grease. Been *seen* with you. Fuckin' informant shit. You think no one *sees* this?" He spreads his arms.

Cuno: "I promise I won't say it." He shakes his head so hard his face turns red. "I won't say any of it anymore."

You: "Precinct 41... what kind of station is it?"
You: "Lieutenant Kitsuragi -- what will you do now?"
You: "Okay. Am I a dirty cop working for La Puta Madre?"
You: "The phasmid -- I need to tell Lena about this ASAP."
You: "Cuno -- what will you do now?"
You: "Wait. I have a *few* questions before you go. About who I am..."
You: "Why did I join the RCM then?"

Volition: Six years and you haven't gotten over it, what the hell is wrong with you?

Jean Vicquemare: "Thank you, Cuno," he says with an amused half-smile. "You're being kind. It's an understaffed station and the district is too big -- which is why we need to..." He tilts his head northward and clicks his tongue.
You: "Did we recently shoot up a church by any chance?" (Point to the church.)
Jean Vicquemare: "So he remembers *that*... Yes, there may have been a raid on *some* churches. It wasn't good press."
Authority: He means it. The RCM and its enemies will not be discussed on this coast.
Shivers: Distant traffic. A scrap of newspaper drifts by, carried by the wind.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Work *with* Pryce?" A crooked smile quivers on his lips. "I'm flattered, but I don't know if I..."
Jean Vicquemare: "We've been hearing whispers in Jamrock too. Ever since fall. I agree that something is happening. People are tense. I hear a fan spinning. Fast. Something is about to hit it."
Cuno: "Not POSSIBLE is me staying here. *Fucking* understand that. I'm not dying here, f****t. I'm coming with you."
Jean Vicquemare: Another sigh -- of surrender.
Esprit de Corps: Even now -- you're his colleague.

Kim Kitsuragi: "I do like the sound of that..." He returns her smile.

Composure: His hands are shaking and his face is white.
